title: For Sale/Trade:  Swedish AG 42 B Ljungman 6.5x55 semi-auto rifle
postcontent:
Swedish AG-42B Ljungman (m42)  for sale. In excellent condition. Matching parts. Bore disk indicates bolt as a 1 (highest rating). Includes bayonet (that can also attach to a Swedish mauser) and night sights.This is an extremely accurate semi-auto; shooting 1.5" at 100yds with the right ammo. I have never had a mechanical problem with it. 

This rifle was one of only 30,000 built in the 40s by the Swedish manufacturer Carl Gustav. Adopted by Sweden's military to compete with other semi-autos of the time such as the Russian svt 40, german gewher and american m1 garand. All but a few rifles were updated to the B configuration in the 1950s. The design was sold to Egypt; who later created the Hakim and Rasheed carbine based on the blueprints. 

I am asking $620 but may consider reasonable offers. This is an excellent example of this rifle. I may consider some trades (see below) for full or partial payment depending on what it is and condition. Email me if you have any questions or call/text REDACTED (Alex)
